<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee/913</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the
                                    Division of Western European Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-08">May 8,
                                    1934</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>The President desires Mr. Norman Davis to go back to Geneva
                                    for the assembling of the Disarmament Conference on the 29th and
                                    to present an expression of the views of this Government.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>I showed the President Ambassador Bingham’s personal telegram
                                    for [<hi rend="italic">from</hi>] Norman Davis, No. 180 of May
                                        4.<note n="16" xml:id="d58fn16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_234">p.
                                            234</ref>.</note> In view of this telegram, which he had
                                    not seen, the President feels we have done all we can towards
                                    meeting the British at the present time.</item>
                            </list>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>